						<summary>

						<p>Slab (No. 5) with a panel of figures in relief, lying in a field to the north of the village.</p>						

						<p>Circa 8th-9th century.</p>						

						<p>This record, which appears to be fragmentary, refers to a gift, free from taxes (<hi rend="italic">? sarva-parihāra</hi>) and to the village Kundanūr. It is in characters of about the 8th-9th century.</p>						

						</summary>
